In this update:
[1] Cholera - Chile (Santiago Metropolitan Region) ex Cuba
[2] Cholera - Venezuela (Venezuelan Capital District) ex Cuba

******
[1] Cholera - Chile (Santiago Province) ex Cuba
Date: Fri 9 Aug 2013
Source: Cooperativa.cl [in Spanish, machine trans., summ., edited]
http://www.cooperativa.cl/noticias/pais/salud/colera/caso-de-colera-importado-desde-cuba-preocupa-a-las-autoridades-sanitarias/2013-08-09/125352.html


The Metropolitan Health official, Rosa Oyarce, has expressed concern about a case of cholera imported from Cuba after leading a sampling of the wastewater plant at the Arturo Merino Benitez International Airport in Pudahuel [Santiago Metropolitan Region].

"There is a high risk of cholera coming to our country from people on vacation," she said, "so the health authority has strengthened controls since yesterday (8 Aug 2013), when the Public Health Institute reported that tests performed on a Chilean citizen who visited Cuba were positive." The patient, 53, has been released and is in good condition according Oyarce.

Oyarce added that "we must not forget that we had 2 deaths in outbreaks of cholera that occurred in Chile in 1998." No cases of cholera had been reported in Chile since 3 cases were reported in 2011.

